<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,303,1592,1618]" box="[189,303,1592,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1592,1618]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1592,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1639,1772]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
A previous Japanese record of this species, from next to the visitor center of Kushiro Shitsugen National Park, 
<collectingRegion box="[258,377,1674,1700]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
, exists in the grey literature (a field guide for a post-symposium field excursion of the 14 
<superScript attach="left" box="[218,231,1708,1722]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">th</superScript>
International Symposium on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[586,707,1710,1737]" class="Ostracoda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="class">Ostracoda</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Hiruta S. &amp; Smith R. J." box="[731,990,1710,1736]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="107 - 125" refId="ref12998" refString="Hiruta S. &amp; Smith R. J. 2001. Living freshwater and shallow marine Ostracoda in Eastern Hokkaido, Japan (Field excursion E). In: Ikeya N. (ed.) Guidebook of Excursions of the 14 th International Symposium on Ostracoda: 107 - 125. Shizuoka University, Shizuoka." type="book chapter" year="2001">Hiruta &amp; Smith 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The additional records presented herein confirm its presence in 
<collectingCountry box="[543,614,1746,1772]" name="Japan" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Japan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="25" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="multiple">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,498,1811,1837]" box="[189,498,1811,1837]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,498,1811,1837]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,498,1811,1837]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ecology and distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1858,2027]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
The Japanese specimens of this species have been found in ponds, a creek, and shallow streams. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Internal" baseAuthorityName="O. F. Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Candona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Candona candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in Eurasia and North America, although rarer in the south (
<bibRefCitation author="Meisch C." box="[1098,1258,1894,1920]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref13462" refString="Meisch C. 2000. Freshwater Ostracoda of Western and Central Europe. Susswasserfauna von Mitteleuropa 8 / 3. Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg." type="book" year="2000">Meisch 2000</bibRefCitation>
), and hence its presence in the cooler part of 
<collectingCountry box="[586,653,1930,1956]" name="Japan" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Japan</collectingCountry>
is not unexpected. It is notable, however, that so far Japanese records are restricted to the eastern part of 
<collectingRegion box="[712,832,1965,1991]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
. The nearest previous records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. Internal" baseAuthorityName="O. F. Muller" baseAuthorityYear="1776" box="[1234,1366,1965,1992]" class="Ostracoda" family="Candonidae" genus="Candona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida">
<emphasis box="[1234,1366,1965,1992]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to eastern 
<collectingRegion box="[281,397,2001,2027]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hokkaido</collectingRegion>
are from the vicinity of Peter the Great Bay, Far East of 
<collectingCountry box="[1082,1160,2001,2027]" name="Russia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schornikov E. I." box="[1177,1386,2001,2027]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="458 - 465" refId="ref13785" refString="Schornikov E. I. 2004. Crustacea: Ostracoda. In: Tyurin A. N. &amp; Drozdov A. L. (eds) Far-Eastern Marine Biospherical Reserve. Biota. V. 2: 458 - 465. Dalnauka, Vladivostok." type="journal article" year="2004">Schornikov 2004</bibRefCitation>
),
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1399,267,331]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
approximately 
<quantity box="[367,472,267,293]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="km" value="1000.0">1000 km</quantity>
due west, and NE 
<collectingRegion box="[701,804,267,293]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[901,979,267,293]" name="Russia" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schornikov E. I. &amp; Trebukhova Y. A." box="[996,1386,267,293]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="56 - 85" refId="ref13702" refString="Schornikov E. I. &amp; Trebukhova Y. A. 2001. Ostracods of brackish and fresh waters of southwestern coast of Peter the Great Bay. In: Kasyanov V. L., Vaschenko M. A. &amp; Pitruk D. L. (eds) The State of Environment and Biota of the Southwestern Part of Peter the Great Bay and the Tumen River Mouth: 56 - 85. Dalnauka, Vladivostok. [In Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2001">Schornikov &amp; Trebukhova 2001</bibRefCitation>
), approximately 
<quantity box="[366,468,305,331]" metricMagnitude="6" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" unit="km" value="1100.0">1100 km</quantity>
north.
</paragraph>
